@startuml unfollowUser
!include ../../theme/theme-dark-seq.puml

title unfollowUser flow
actor User
participant Resolver
participant FollowsService as F
participant ActivityService as A
database DB

User -> Resolver: unfollowUser()
Resolver -> F: unfollow() : bool

group followRepo.manager.transaction
  F -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> F: follower | null

  F -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> F: following | null

  note over F,DB
  Overall flow:
  - if follower/following missing, return false
  - if no follow exists, return success immediately
  - otherwise remove the follow row
  - then log follow activity as inactive
  end note

  alt follower or following missing
    F --> Resolver: false
    Resolver --> User: data.unfollowUser = false
  else lookup existing follow
    F -> DB: manager.findOne(Follow)
    DB --> F: follow | null

    alt no existing follow
      F --> Resolver: true
      Resolver --> User: data.unfollowUser = true
    else follow exists
      F -> DB: manager.remove(Follow)
      DB --> F: follow removed

      F -> A: logActivity()
      A -> DB: repo.query()
      DB --> A: activity row
      A --> F: activity

      F --> Resolver: true
      Resolver --> User: data.unfollowUser = true
    end
  end
end

== Error rule ==
note over F,DB
If any awaited step inside the transaction throws:
TypeORM issues ROLLBACK, then error bubbles to resolver,
and resolver returns a GraphQL error.
end note
@enduml
